title: Facebook Rebrands its Crypto Wallet
text: Facebook has renamed its digital wallet Novi, drawing from Latin words that mean new and way.

title: Facebook renames its digital cryptocurrency wallet Novi
text: No longer Calibra, the digital wallet's previously controversial logo also gets a redesign.

title: Facebook launches CatchUp, an experimental app for voice calls
text: The social media giant's NPE team tests a new way to make group calls.

title: Facebook stock heads toward longest winning streak since 2015
text: Facebook Inc. shares FB, +0.69% are up 0.6% in Tuesday trading and on track for their eighth straight trading day of gains.

title: Facebook launches CatchUp, an audio-only group calling app that shows who’s ready to chat now
text: Facebook’s internal R&D group, NPE Team, has today launched a new app called CatchUp that makes it easier for friends and family in the U.S. to coordinate phone calls or set up group calls with up to 8 people.

title: Facebook rebrands Libra wallet Calibra to Novi
text: When Facebook unveiled Libra, its cryptocurrency project, there were two distinct entities — the Libra Association, a not-for-profit that oversees all things Libra, and Calibra, a Facebook subsidiary that is building a Libra-based wallet with integrations in WhatsApp and Messenger. Today, Facebook announced that Calibra has a new name, Novi.

title: Facebook Novi is the new name for service that will let people send Libra digital currency to one another
text: Facebook is launching a cryptocurrency called Libra, with the intention of making it easier for people to send money across the world. While Libra will be run by a nonprofit association supported by a range of companies and organizations, Facebook will operate Novi.
